name: A Full Recovery is Made in Cairo - 11"x14"
description:
May 12, 1908: What a sight to behold! With only six cars remaining in the last leg of the race, car #5, Team Bear (Canada) is passed by the last of its competing autos. The pair's racer had suffered unknown damages in the middle of the Sahara and was moving only with the help  of a hired camel. Imagine the surprise for the other racers when Team Bear pulled into the lead just outside the borders of Cairo! That's one for the books boys! 

A Full Recovery is Made in Cairo, signed 11"x14" giclee print on watercolor paper. Printed in very limited numbers by the good folks at Zerofriends Art Collective.

name: Freedom Through Innovation - 8"x10" print
description:
March 1st, 1908: In Car #3, Team Raven! From Germany, this pair has developed what they believe to be the height of motorcar technology. Only time will tell if they are right as they push on through the first race from New York to Marrakesh! 

8"x10" signed giclee print on watercolor paper. Printed by the good folks at Zerofriends Art collective.

name: The Lost Ring and The Very Resourceful Suitor
description: The Lost Ring and The Very Resourceful Suitor 100 prints are being made available to anyone who loves life, love and/or good times in San Francisco. All Proceeds go towards the artist and his new fiance living Happily Ever After! The Lost Ring was painted (and etched) with ink and acrylics on Claybord. Each print comes signed and numbered. Prints will be packaged up with a hug and shipped to you on February 7th (USPS Priority mail).

name: Bear Back Rider - Art Print
description: Bear Back Rider She's a wild woman! These giclee prints are produced with museum-quality archival inks on Acid Free Velvet Cotton Rag Paper. Signed.
